==[[Boxing]]== '''Events''' * 4 June — Harry Sellers retained his English championship against Joe Hood in a 1 hour fight at [[Ascot Heath]].<ref name=HS>[http://www.cyberboxingzone.com/boxing/sellers-harry.htm Cyber Boxing Zone – Harry Sellers]. Retrieved on 7 November 2009.</ref> * 2 July — Harry Sellers retained his English championship against Joe Hood in a 30 minute fight at [[Ipswich]].<ref name=HS/>
==[[Cricket]]== '''Events''' * [[James Aylward (cricketer)|James Aylward]] scored 167 for [[Hampshire county cricket teams|Hampshire]] against an [[Non-international England cricket teams|England XI]] at [[Vine Cricket Ground|Sevenoaks Vine]] to create a new record for the highest individual innings in [[First-class cricket#Important matches classification|first-class cricket]]. The record stood until 1806. '''England''' * Most runs<ref name="cards">Note that scorecards created in the 18th century are not necessarily accurate or complete; therefore any summary of runs, wickets or catches can only represent the '''known''' totals and the missing data prevents effective computation of averages</ref> – [[James Aylward (cricketer)|James Aylward]] 390 * Most wickets<ref name="cards"/> – [[Thomas Brett (cricketer)|Thomas Brett]] 29
