{{Infobox IcehockeyTeamSeason |Season=1916–17 |year=1916 |Team=Toronto Hockey Club |League=NHA |Conference= |ConferenceRank= |Division= |DivisionRank= |Record=7–7–0 |HomeRecord=4–3–0 |RoadRecord=3–4–0 |GoalsFor=64 |GoalsAgainst=61 |GeneralManager= |Coach= |Captain= |AltCaptain= |Arena=[[Mutual Street Arena|Arena Gardens]] |Attendance= |GoalsLeader= |AssistsLeader= |PointsLeader= |PlusMinusLeader= |PIMLeader= |WinsLeader= |GAALeader= |StanleyCup= }}
The '''[[1916–17 NHA season|1916–17]] [[Toronto Blueshirts|Toronto Hockey Club]] season''' was the fifth and final season of the Toronto franchise in the [[National Hockey Association]] (NHA). With the departure of the [[Toronto 228th Battalion (NHA)|Toronto 228th Battalion]] when their regiment was ordered overseas, the NHA decided to suspend the Toronto Blueshirts franchise as well for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite book |last=Coleman|first=Charles|title=The Trail of the Stanley Cup, Vol. 1, 1893–1926 inc.|year=1966|publisher=NHL|page=311}}</ref> Before the start of the next season, the NHA folded and a new league, the [[National Hockey League]] (NHL), was founded with a new team, the [[Toronto Arenas|Toronto Hockey Club]], which went on to become the present day [[Toronto Maple Leafs]].<ref>{{Cite book|first=Morey |last=Holzman |author2=Joseph Nieforth |title=Deceptions and Doublecross: How the NHL Conquered Hockey |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=COb82MiKyGQC&lpg=PP1&dq=Deceptions%20and%20Doublecross%3A%20How%20the%20NHL%20Conquered%20Hockey&pg=PP1#v=onepage&q&f=true|year=2002 |location=Toronto, ON, Canada |publisher=Dundurn Press |isbn=1-55002-413-2 |ref=harv |page=159}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=McKinley |first=Michael |year=2006|title=Hockey: A People's History|publisher=McClelland & Stewart|isbn= 0-7710-5769-5|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fCAL2ysKFWoC&lpg=PP1&dq=Hockey%3A%20A%20People's%20History&pg=PP1#v=onepage&q&f=true |ref=harv|page=77}}</ref> {{TOClimit|limit=2}}
