{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = West Cliff | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Preston, Lancashire]] | establishment = 1870 | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1936–1939 & 1952 | club1 = [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]] | date = 4 September | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/699.html profile }}
'''West Cliff''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Preston, Lancashire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1870, when Preston played a [[United North of England Eleven]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/699_misc.html Other matches played on West Cliff]</ref>
In 1936, the ground held its first [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match when [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]] played [[Gloucestershire County Cricket Club|Gloucestershire]]. From 1936 to 1939, the ground played host to 4 first-class matches involving Lancashire, the last of which saw them play [[Glamorgan County Cricket Club|Glamorgan]]. In 1952, Lancashire returned to the ground where they played a single first-class match against Glamorgan.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/699_f.html First-Class Matches played on West Cliff]</ref>
The ground has also played host to a combined total of 15 Second XI fixtures for the Lancashire Second XI in the [[Minor Counties Championship]], [[Second XI Championship]] and Second XI Trophy.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/699_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on West Cliff]</ref><ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/699_sec.html Second XI Championship Matches played on West Cliff]</ref><ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/699_set.html Second XI Trophy Matches played on West Cliff]</ref>
Still in use to this day, in local domestic cricket the ground is the home venue of [[Preston Cricket Club]]<ref>[http://preston.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp? Preston Cricket Club]</ref> who play in the [[Northern Premier Cricket League]].
